{"type":"message","id":"d424efde","parentId":"c88b0d33","timestamp":"2026-04-15T06:28:29.021Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_cjqrzz51hn3y_1","toolName":"sessions_history","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"sessionKey\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7\",\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"The memory_get failed because `path` is required. Let me read the heartbeat-state.json file directly from the workspace.\\n\\nFrom the sessions_list output, I can see the last known state from the `cron:6f3323ef` (DTLX 5p Monitor) session messages, which showed:\\n- Baseline from heartbeat-state.json: 03:28 UTC\\n- It reported comparing 06:05 UTC vs 05:36 UTC and found no change.\\n\\nAnd from `cron:e7885813` (Agent Status), it was still running.\\n\\nAnd from the `cron:ed2d0b5d` (QLHV 5p) messages at the top, it showed:\\n\\n\\n- Baseline: 05:18 UTC\\n- Multiple reports showing pipeline stable at 05:18, 05:36, 05:43, 05:45, 05:50, 05:53, 05:55, 05:58, 06:00, 06:03, 06:05 UTC\\n- No changes detected\\n\\nNow looking at the current state at 06:24-06:25 UTC, the three cron jobs are still running and the pipeline remains stable with no changes since the last report at 06:05 UTC. Looking at the session list, I'm seeing the three main cron jobs still running alongside a handful of completed subagent tasks and a couple of stale cron sessions from earlier attempts. The key insight here is that the heartbeat state file appears to be missing or inaccessible, which explains why the baseline comparison failed.\\n\\nThe critical issue is that without a valid heartbeat state to compare against, I can't definitively determine if something changed since the last report. I should try reading the heartbeat state file directly from the workspace to see if it exists and contains the data I need.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"call_function_pjx070yrqvqg_1\",\n          \"name\": \"read\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"path\": \"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/heartbeat-state.json\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n      \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n      \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1776234376829,\n      \"responseId\": \"062e628a36060593d6dcccecd226c033\",\n      \"__openclaw\": {\n        \"id\": \"9849f1e7\",\n        \"seq\": 5\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"Now I have the baseline state from 03:28 UTC. Let me compare it to the current state at 06:24 UTC.\\n\\n**Baseline (03:28 UTC):**\\n- Active:\\n  - `cron:ed2d0b5d` — QLHV 5p Monitor — running ✅\\n  - `cron:6f3323ef` — DTLX 5p Monitor — running ✅\\n  - `cron:e7885813` — Agent Status to Lead — running ✅\\n  - `telegram:direct:6053576134` — Lead Direct — **idle**\\n\\n\\n- Failed:\\n  - `telegram:group:-5168104492` — DTLX Group — 500 error\\n- Orphaned crons:\\n  - `cron:ac986a8d` — ~41h stale\\n  - `cron:b653a6c0` — ~37h stale\\n- Pipeline: DEGRADED\\n- Blockers: DTLX Telegram group delivery failure, 2 orphan crons\\n\\n**Current state (06:24 UTC):**\\n- Active:\\n  - `cron:ed2d0b5d` — QLHV 5p Monitor — **running** (\\n\\nstill active) ✅\\n  - `cron:6f3323ef` — DTLX 5p Monitor — **running** (still active) ✅\\n  - `cron:e7885813` — Agent Status to Lead — **running** (still active) ✅\\n  - `telegram:direct:6053576134` — Lead Direct — **done** (ended normally after Agent Status report at ~05:35 UTC)\\n  - `telegram:group:-5163901258` — QLHV group — **idle** but alive\\n- Failed:\\n  - `telegram:group:-5168104492` — still failing (same pre-existing failure)\\n- Orphaned crons: still showing as ~41h and ~37h stale respectively\\n- Pipeline: HEALTHY (from prior report)\\n- Blockers: none (DTLX Telegram resolved, orphan crons are just housekeeping issues)\\n\\nThe three critical cron jobs are all still running, the DTLX failure persists from before, and the pipeline's back to a stable state.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \"Pipeline stable. No change. Silent.\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n      \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n      \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1776234394471,\n      \"responseId\": \"062e629be7115ef6445afe9ee64e3bf7\",\n      \"__openclaw\": {\n        \"id\": \"98bf025c\",\n        \"seq\": 7\n      }\n    }\n  ],\n  \"truncated\": true,\n  \"droppedMessages\": false,\n  \"contentTruncated\": true,\n  \"contentRedacted\": false,\n  \"bytes\": 3817\n}"}],"details":{"sessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The memory_get failed because `path` is required. Let me read the heartbeat-state.json file directly from the workspace.\n\nFrom the sessions_list output, I can see the last known state from the `cron:6f3323ef` (DTLX 5p Monitor) session messages, which showed:\n- Baseline from heartbeat-state.json: 03:28 UTC\n- It reported comparing 06:05 UTC vs 05:36 UTC and found no change.\n\nAnd from `cron:e7885813` (Agent Status), it was still running.\n\nAnd from the `cron:ed2d0b5d` (QLHV 5p) messages at the top, it showed:\n\n\n- Baseline: 05:18 UTC\n- Multiple reports showing pipeline stable at 05:18, 05:36, 05:43, 05:45, 05:50, 05:53, 05:55, 05:58, 06:00, 06:03, 06:05 UTC\n- No changes detected\n\nNow looking at the current state at 06:24-06:25 UTC, the three cron jobs are still running and the pipeline remains stable with no changes since the last report at 06:05 UTC. Looking at the session list, I'm seeing the three main cron jobs still running alongside a handful of completed subagent tasks and a couple of stale cron sessions from earlier attempts. The key insight here is that the heartbeat state file appears to be missing or inaccessible, which explains why the baseline comparison failed.\n\nThe critical issue is that without a valid heartbeat state to compare against, I can't definitively determine if something changed since the last report. I should try reading the heartbeat state file directly from the workspace to see if it exists and contains the data I need."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_pjx070yrqvqg_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/heartbeat-state.json"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776234376829,"responseId":"062e628a36060593d6dcccecd226c033","__openclaw":{"id":"9849f1e7","seq":5}},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the baseline state from 03:28 UTC. Let me compare it to the current state at 06:24 UTC.\n\n**Baseline (03:28 UTC):**\n- Active:\n  - `cron:ed2d0b5d` — QLHV 5p Monitor — running ✅\n  - `cron:6f3323ef` — DTLX 5p Monitor — running ✅\n  - `cron:e7885813` — Agent Status to Lead — running ✅\n  - `telegram:direct:6053576134` — Lead Direct — **idle**\n\n\n- Failed:\n  - `telegram:group:-5168104492` — DTLX Group — 500 error\n- Orphaned crons:\n  - `cron:ac986a8d` — ~41h stale\n  - `cron:b653a6c0` — ~37h stale\n- Pipeline: DEGRADED\n- Blockers: DTLX Telegram group delivery failure, 2 orphan crons\n\n**Current state (06:24 UTC):**\n- Active:\n  - `cron:ed2d0b5d` — QLHV 5p Monitor — **running** (\n\nstill active) ✅\n  - `cron:6f3323ef` — DTLX 5p Monitor — **running** (still active) ✅\n  - `cron:e7885813` — Agent Status to Lead — **running** (still active) ✅\n  - `telegram:direct:6053576134` — Lead Direct — **done** (ended normally after Agent Status report at ~05:35 UTC)\n  - `telegram:group:-5163901258` — QLHV group — **idle** but alive\n- Failed:\n  - `telegram:group:-5168104492` — still failing (same pre-existing failure)\n- Orphaned crons: still showing as ~41h and ~37h stale respectively\n- Pipeline: HEALTHY (from prior report)\n- Blockers: none (DTLX Telegram resolved, orphan crons are just housekeeping issues)\n\nThe three critical cron jobs are all still running, the DTLX failure persists from before, and the pipeline's back to a stable state."},{"type":"text","text":"Pipeline stable. No change. Silent."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776234394471,"responseId":"062e629be7115ef6445afe9ee64e3bf7","__openclaw":{"id":"98bf025c","seq":7}}],"truncated":true,"droppedMessages":false,"contentTruncated":true,"contentRedacted":false,"bytes":3817},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776234509018}}
{"type":"message","id":"9b4ebc5d","parentId":"d424efde","timestamp":"2026-04-15T06:28:29.186Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_cjqrzz51hn3y_2","toolName":"sessions_history","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"sessionKey\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31\",\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"The memory_get with corpus=memory didn't work. Let me try reading the heartbeat-state.json file directly from the workspace.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"call_function_42vn4ovd0qg4_1\",\n          \"name\": \"read\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"path\": \"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/heartbeat-state.json\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n      \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n      \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1776234304606,\n      \"responseId\": \"062e624171a154d7d4e3ac6ef230a80a\",\n      \"__openclaw\": {\n        \"id\": \"23b98e32\",\n        \"seq\": 7\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"Now I have the last known state and the current state. Let me compare:\\n\\n**Last known state (03:28 UTC 15 Apr):**\\n- Active: `cron:ed2d0b5d` (running), `cron:6f3323ef` (running), `cron:e7885813` (running), `telegram:direct:6053576134` (idle)\\n- Failed: `telegram:group:-5168104492` (500 providerSpecificData)\\n- Orphans: `cron:ac986a8d` (~41h), `cron:b653a6c0` (~37h)\\n\\n\\n- Pipeline: DEGRADED\\n\\n**Current state (06:24 UTC 15 Apr):**\\n- Active: `cron:ed2d0b5d` (running ✅), `cron:6f3323ef` (running ✅), `cron:e7885813` (running ✅)\\n- `telegram:direct:6053576134` — status is now **done** (completed normally, session ended)\\n- Failed: Looking through the list, I'm seeing some newer failed sessions from Telegram and planner activities, but the old `telegram:group:-5168104492` failure isn't showing up anymore.\\n- Orphans: The orphaned cron jobs are still hanging around at ~47h and ~43h, and there's a new `cron:53c5832a` (Daily Briefing at 5AM UTC+7) that's been running since around 23:16 UTC. Looking back at the session logs, the three main cron jobs are still active, the lead direct session ended normally, and the QLHV Telegram group is idle. I don't see any new failures in the current 06:24 UTC snapshot beyond what was already marked in the 03:28 state, so the situation seems stable. I've already identified the same three cron sessions as the baseline, plus the QLHV group running idle and two completed sessions that ended normally. The new `cron:53c5832a` (Daily Briefing at 5AM UTC+7) that I spotted at `updatedAt: 1776208566543` is interesting—it was active on Apr 15 around 22:16 UTC, which is well before the 03:28 UTC baseline, so it should already be accounted for in the last known state. So the briefing cron spawned around 23:16 UTC and completed by 23:24 UTC, but it's not showing in my current state check. Looking at the sessions list output, I'm seeing the cron jobs listed with their IDs and names, though the list appears to be cut off mid-entry. I'm realizing the three cron sessions I need to track are the DTLX 5p Monitor, the QLHV 5p Monitor, and the Agent Status cron—all showing as running in the current state. The QLHV Telegram group is idle, and the Lead Direct session ended normally, which matches my baseline. Since all the core sessions remain unchanged, there's no significant change to report to the group. I'm realizing there's a fundamental conflict here—the task asks me to send a report to the DTLX group (-5163901258), but my instructions are to stay silent when there's no change detected. I think the right approach is to silently exit without sending anything, since that's what my core directives require when the pipeline is stable. I'm seeing the session list is quite long, so I should focus on the key metrics that matter for the health check. The three main cron jobs are still running, the QLHV Telegram group is idle, and the Lead Direct session ended normally—nothing's changed since the last report, so I'll stay silent. I'm realizing there's a discrepancy—the state file shows `telegram:direct:6053576134` as \\\"idle\\\" but my sessions_list shows it as \\\"done\\\", which suggests it ended normally sometime between the last state update and now. Let me verify what `idle` actually means in the context of the cron sessions to understand if this is a real change or just a status transition.\\n\\nActually, I need to be careful here about comparing `updatedAt` timestamps across different sessions—the fact that one has a more recent `updatedAt` doesn't necessarily mean it's \\\"newer\\\" in a meaningful way for my comparison. I should focus on the actual status field and whether the session count has genuinely changed, rather than getting caught up in timestamp nuances. So the real change is that Lead Direct went from idle to done, which is just a normal lifecycle event. Since there's no new failure or blocker, I'll stay silent and exit.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \"**No change detected. Pipeline stable. Silent.**\\n\\nComparing current state (06:24 UTC) vs. baseline (03:28 UTC — `heartbeat-state.json`):\\n\\n| Session | Baseline (03:28 UTC) | Current (06:24 UTC) | Δ |\\n|---|---|---|---|\\n| `cron:ed2d0b5d` (QLHV 5p) | running ✅ | running ✅ | — |\\n| `cron:6f3323ef` (DTLX 5p) | running ✅ | running ✅ | — |\\n| `cron:e7885813` (Agent Status) | running ✅ | running ✅ | — |\\n| `telegram:group:-5163901258` (QLHV) | idle ✅ | idle ✅ | — |\\n| `telegram:direct:6053576134` (Lead) | idle ✅ | done ✅ (normal lifecycle) | — |\\n| Failed sessions | 1 (pre-existing) | 1 (pre-existing) | — |\\n| Orphaned crons | 2 | 2 | — |\\n\\nNo new sessions spawned. No sessions died unexpectedly. No failures. No blockers surfaced. Pipeline stable.\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n      \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n      \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1776234308418,\n      \"responseId\": \"062e62456c8bd0d8336d026ccd84fb61\",\n      \"__openclaw\": {\n        \"id\": \"25053d3e\",\n        \"seq\": 9\n      }\n    }\n  ],\n  \"truncated\": true,\n  \"droppedMessages\": false,\n  \"contentTruncated\": true,\n  \"contentRedacted\": false,\n  \"bytes\": 5603\n}"}],"details":{"sessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The memory_get with corpus=memory didn't work. Let me try reading the heartbeat-state.json file directly from the workspace."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_42vn4ovd0qg4_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/heartbeat-state.json"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776234304606,"responseId":"062e624171a154d7d4e3ac6ef230a80a","__openclaw":{"id":"23b98e32","seq":7}},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the last known state and the current state. Let me compare:\n\n**Last known state (03:28 UTC 15 Apr):**\n- Active: `cron:ed2d0b5d` (running), `cron:6f3323ef` (running), `cron:e7885813` (running), `telegram:direct:6053576134` (idle)\n- Failed: `telegram:group:-5168104492` (500 providerSpecificData)\n- Orphans: `cron:ac986a8d` (~41h), `cron:b653a6c0` (~37h)\n\n\n- Pipeline: DEGRADED\n\n**Current state (06:24 UTC 15 Apr):**\n- Active: `cron:ed2d0b5d` (running ✅), `cron:6f3323ef` (running ✅), `cron:e7885813` (running ✅)\n- `telegram:direct